children.subject:
It sounds like quite a bit of work. 188 eats up time with its consistent projects (debugging is the culprit). 16b will likewise eat up time since you'll probably need to go over the material more than once to get it.

70 is your real priority, so you might need to neglect the other 2 classes if your time gets strained. That being said, a B+ is, by all means, achievable as long as you are the mean or slightly above the mean on the tests.

If you have nothing outside of classes, I think you can do it. If you're recruiting, consider leaving 188 or 16b for another time.

history.content: Hey is eecs 16b, cs70, cs188 & a breadth too much? I need a B+ in 70 and I am retaking it (I dropped the course this summer ~ went through most of the material with average understanding). If it is too much I am trying to figure out whether I should drop 16b or 188. I can't tell right now since school just started, but I know things start picking up during the middle of the semester & I feel like it may backfire on me. But I'm trying to push my limits at the same time.
